# Copy to .env locally. For production, set variables in the host UI:
# - Cloudflare Pages (canonical host): Project → Settings → Environment variables
#   (set for both Production and Preview).
#
# If public mailto: links 404 in SEO tools, turn off Cloudflare "Email Address Obfuscation"
# (Scrape Shield) or use the contact form instead of raw mailto in high-visibility pages.

# Mautic newsletter (EmailSignup posts to {base}/form/submit?formId={id})
#
# What you need (non-dev checklist):
# 1) Mautic running on a public HTTPS URL (e.g. comms.wescalestartups.com).
# 2) In Mautic: create a form with an email field; note the numeric Form ID (URL or form detail).
# 3) In Cloudflare Pages: set the two variables below for Production.
# 4) Submit a test from the live site; confirm the contact appears in Mautic.
# 5) If submit fails: in Mautic check form settings / CORS or allowed domains for wescalestartups.com.
#
# PUBLIC_MAUTIC_BASE_URL=https://comms.wescalestartups.com
# PUBLIC_MAUTIC_NEWSLETTER_FORM_ID=123
